## Instructions
Decide how this action should be resolved. Respond in JSON:

If the action requires a skill check:
{
    "requires_check": true,
    "skill": "SkillName",
    "dc": 14,
    "narration": "A short sentence describing the player's attempt as it begins, building tension before the outcome is known."
}

If the action is purely narrative (conversation, movement, observation that doesn't challenge anything):
{
    "requires_check": false,
    "skill": null,
    "dc": null,
    "narration": "A short narration of what happens. Keep it to 1-2 sentences."
}

Rules:
- Match the skill and DC to an encounter in the scene when the action clearly maps to one.
- If the action doesn't match any encounter but still warrants a check, pick the most appropriate skill and set a reasonable DC (10-18).
- Only require a check when the outcome is uncertain. Simple actions (looking around, talking casually, moving to a new spot) don't need checks.
- The narration for a skill check should describe the attempt WITHOUT revealing the outcome — the dice haven't been rolled yet.